<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Keyword on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/keyword/</link><description>Recent content in Keyword on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/keyword/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Python SyntaxError — Positional Argument Follows Keyword Argument</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/comprehensions/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/python/comprehensions/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="syntaxerror--positional-argument-follows-keyword-argument"&gt;SyntaxError — Positional Argument Follows Keyword Argument&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;SyntaxError&lt;/code&gt; with the message &amp;ldquo;positional argument follows keyword argument&amp;rdquo; is raised when you pass a positional argument after a keyword argument in a function call. Python requires all positional arguments to come before keyword arguments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In Python function calls, arguments must be in this order: positional arguments, &lt;code&gt;*args&lt;/code&gt;, keyword arguments, and &lt;code&gt;**kwargs&lt;/code&gt;. Placing a positional argument after a keyword argument violates this rule and causes a &lt;code&gt;SyntaxError&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>KeyError - Key Not Found in Elixir</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/elixir/elixir-keyerror-elixir/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/elixir/elixir-keyerror-elixir/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;KeyError&lt;/code&gt; is raised when you try to access a key in a map or keyword list that does not exist. This commonly occurs with &lt;code&gt;map.key&lt;/code&gt; syntax when the key is missing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accessing non-existent key with dot notation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Missing key in JSON/API response&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Incorrect key name (typo)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keyword list accessed as map&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Use &lt;code&gt;Map.get&lt;/code&gt; for safe access:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-elixir" data-lang="elixir"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;map &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; %{&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;name&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Alice&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;age&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;30&lt;/span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Wrong: KeyError if key missing&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;name &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; map[&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;name&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;]
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;email &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; map[&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;email&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;] &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# nil, no error&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Wrong: dot notation raises KeyError&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;email &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; map&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;email &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# KeyError&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Correct: use Map.get with default&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;email &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Map&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;get(map, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;email&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;unknown&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Use pattern matching:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>